Features

ETL Pipeline:

Imports Pokémon data from CSV files into a PostgreSQL database.

Cleans and formats data for efficient querying.

Handles missing values and duplicate entries.

Database:

PostgreSQL database storing all Pokémon attributes, abilities, evolutions, and types.

Normalized tables to reduce redundancy.

Supports complex queries and filtering.

GUI:

Python Tkinter-based interface for interactive exploration.

Search Pokémon by name, type, generation, or abilities.

Displays results in a user-friendly table format.

AI Integration:

Uses a local Ollama model to translate natural language questions into SQL queries.

Answers questions like “What Pokémon have the ability Levitate?” or “Show all Generation 3 Water-types.”

Generates narrative-style responses in Pokémon language.
